title.narrative: 503 EDUCATION FOR OUT OF SCHOOL GIRLS AND BOYS

description.narrative: Government and partners have increased capacity to deliver gender responsive and equitable, flexible, inclusive quality elementary education for out of school girls and boys, which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Access To Quality Learning Opportunities (Covid), Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Business and Key Business Stakeholders demonstrate growing willingness, commitment and resource allocation for protecting and promoting child rights in policy and practice by 2022

title.narrative: Government and partners have increased capacity to deliver gender responsive and equitable, flexible, inclusive qualityelementary education for out of school girls and boys

description.narrative: In collaboration with government and partners,193,010 previously ; out-of-school children (44% girls) identified and referred to formal education mainstreaming in eleven states/union territories despite the prolonged school closures in 2021. Constant capacity development of school staff on the use of state customized out-of-school mobile application (App) and investing in structured outreach activities and campaigns to mobilise community engagement and participation in facilitating the identification of out-of-school children enabled this result. The App profiles the vulnerabilities of children (i.e. migration, disabilities, labor, gender) to address potential learning support and needs of children to be retained in schools in the future. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:09/01/2022
